SUMMARY:Art in Action: Spectacular Seed Bombs
DESCRIPTION:Pence Family Art Workshops\nLearn about the ancient Japanese p
 ractice of seed bombs! Using air-dry clay and native wildflower seeds\, ma
 ke seed bombs that you can later plant outdoors or in a garden. Decorate y
 our seed bombs with dried petals and stamps\, and design and illustrate a 
 plant care card to help you take care of the wildflowers you plant.\n\nArt
  in Action: Spectacular Seed Bombs\nSaturday\, May 30\, 1-3 PM\n$5 Members
 \, $10 Non-Members (per person\, all materials included)\n\n**How it works
 :**\nArt in Action engages kids in art projects that are fun\, creative\, 
 and collaborative with their family members. This is a drop-in program for
  ages 5-12. No registration in advance is required\, but space and supplie
 s are limited to the first 25 participants and are available on a first co
 me\, first served basis.\n\nWhen you arrive\, pay with cash or card at the
  front desk. A parent or adult caregiver is required to stay\, but only ha
 s to pay for the project for themselves if they are also doing art. Stay a
 s long or as short as you like over the two hour period.\n\nBecome a Membe
 r starting at $70/year and save! If you join the Pence Gallery when you at
 tend this workshop\, you can enjoy Member pricing for Art in Action\, plus
  receive a $5 gift certificate to our gift shop as a thank you. Membership
  supports art for all ages and makes creative moments like this possible
 —jump in and be part of it.\n\nWe have a different Art in Action family 
 workshop every month! Learn more at [https://pencegallery.org/art-in-actio
 n/](https://pencegallery.org/art-in-action/).\n\nThis unique monthly progr
 am is generously sponsored and made possible by Mary Stephens DeWall and L
 es DeWall.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/art-in-action/events/314058525/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260331T190727Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260331T190727Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
